                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>As of 2013 there are <me>1.21\times10^{13}  = 1\overbrace{2{,}100{,}000{,}000{,}000}^{13\text{ places}}</me> known digits of <m>\pi</m>.</p>
                            </li>
                        </ol></p>
                    </solution>
